Latino Foods Frontera Green Chili Enchilada Sauce
items.directions:
Quick recipe. Makes 4 enchiladas.
Green chile & cheese enchiladas.
4 corn tortillas.
About 1 1/2 cups shredded chihuahua or Monterey Jack cheese.
1 pouch Frontera enchilada sauce.
1. Heat oven to 400 degrees. Wrap tortillas in plastic wrap. Microwave until steamy, about 30 sec.
2. Roll 1/4 cup cheese into each warm tortilla.
Place side by side in small baking dish or pie dish, seam-side down.
3. Completely cover with sauce. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake 15 min.
Variation: substitute cooked vegetables, chicken, beef or pork for cheese in the filling.
items.ingredients: Tomatillos, Water, Poblano, Chiles, Onion, Heavy Cream, Lime Juice from Concentrate, Cilantro, Garlic, Salt, Serrano Peppers, Evaporated Cane Juice, Xanthan Gum.

items.name: Latino Foods Little Bear Taco Seasoning
items.directions: To Prepare Tacos: 1. In a large skillet, brown 1 pound ground turkey until crumbly. 2. Add Bearitos Taco Seasoning, 2/3 cup water. Blend well. 3. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, simmer uncovered, 8-10 minutes. Stir occasionally. 4. Spoon taco filling into warmed Bearitos taco shells. Top with shredded lettuce, grated cheddar cheese, diced tomatoes and salsa or taco sauce. Makes about 3 cups of filling, enough for 12 tacos, (3 Tbsp. filling each).
items.ingredients: Dehydrated Onion, Salt, Dehydrated Garlic, Corn Meal, Spices, Chili Peppers, Paprika, Autolyzed Yeast Extract.

items.name: Latino Foods Simply Organic Fajita Seasoning
items.directions: 1. Mix packet contents with 1/4 cup warm water in a bowl, stir until completely dissolved. 2. Place 1/4 in. strips of chicken (1 lb. of boneless breast) in a plastic bag. Add 2 tbsp. of vegetable oil to bag and coat chicken. Add fajita marinade to bag and coat chicken again. 3. In a large skillet, thoroughly cook marinated chicken. Add sliced onion, and sliced green or red peppers. Cook for an additional 3 - 5 minutes. Makes 4, two-fajita, servings.

Latino Foods De La Estancia Polenta With Garlic & Scallions
items.display_name: De La Estancia Polenta With Garlic & Scallions
items.directions: Keep cool and dry and, once opened, store in an airtight container. Basic Polenta Recipe: 4-5 portions. Ingredients: 1 cup (150 grams) of polenta; 3 cups (720 ml) broth; 3 tablespoons of grated parmesan cheese (optional). Bring the broth just to a simmer in a saucepan. Add the polenta in a thin stream stirring all the while with a spoon over medium heat. Continue stirring for about 2 minutes until the polenta just separates from the sides of the pan. Add the cheese if using and continue stirring until the cheese has disappeared. Serve hot directly from the pot or with any sauce that you would serve with pasta or rice.
